-- Petrofac Chairman resigns for compassionate reasons
-- By Karolin Schaps
-- Fri Aug 22, 2014 02:13AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Aug 22 (Reuters) - The Chairman of British oil and gas service group Petrofac <PFC.L>, Norman Murray, has resigned with immediate effect due to compassionate reasons, the company said on Friday.

Murray will be replaced by Senior Independent Director Rijnhard van Tets who in turn will be succeeded by Non-Executive Director Thomas Thune Andersen in his current role.